commit 1716ef40ef9ec550208d0adcdb71c94167b99b93
Author: Markus Hrywniak <mhrywniak@nvidia.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 25 05:41:18 2019 -0700

    Add switch to use offsets, add new optimized path

    * Adapted signature of loadDistributedMatrix to use new parameter struct
      * Needed to adapt glue.h and example to adapt to new signature
    * Added existing partition-map based approach as loadDistributedMatrixPartitionVec
        and new offset-based routine as loadDistributedMatrixPartitionOffsets
    * Renamed struct routines to use "AMGX_distribution_..." prefix for consistency
      * C setter routines for partition vector and offsets

    The optimized path can be chosen by supplying a list of partition offsets in case the matrix
    has a contiguous partitioning across all MPI ranks:
    * Rank 0 has rows 0..partition[1]-1, rank 1 rows partition[1]..partition[2]-1, and so on
    * Remove partition_map and ipartition_map, both are a no-op (contain
      0..num_rows_global for this partitioning)
    * Make allocation of my_indices only depend on local row count by shifting
      indices so they are always in range. Allows to:
    * Eliminate partitionVec, replace with lookup function. We know the start and end
      of our local row indices, so instead of generating a lookup table, just use a
